{"word":"ἐπικλάω","slug":"ἐπικλάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπικλάω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>άσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to bend to</i> or <i>besides</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be bent double</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to bow down</i>, <el>τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἐπικλασθῆναι τῇ γνώμῃ</el> <i>to be broken in spirit</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; but also, <i>to be bent</i> or <i>turned to pity</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}